---
description: Compute path_prefix from $_SERVER['SCRIPT_NAME'] and use it for static asset URLs in header and footer
globs: **/*.php
alwaysApply: false
---

- **Pages in subdirectories MUST resolve static assets using `$path_prefix`**
  - `V:\includes\header.php` computes `$path_prefix` and uses it for `css/` and `js/` includes.
  - `V:\includes\footer.php` recomputes the same `$path_prefix` for footer links and scripts.
  - New/edited PHP that emits asset URLs **MUST** use this `$path_prefix` pattern; do not hardcode `../` chains.

- **Canonical computation (match `header.php` / `footer.php`)**
  - Source of truth: [V:\includes\header.php](mdc:includes/header.php) lines 30-45 and [V:\includes\footer.php](mdc:includes/footer.php) lines 7-17.

```php
$script_name = $_SERVER['SCRIPT_NAME'];
$script_dir = dirname($script_name);

if ($script_dir === '/') {
    $path_prefix = '';
} else {
    $path_segments = trim($script_dir, '/');
    $segment_count = $path_segments === '' ? 0 : substr_count($path_segments, '/') + 1;
    $path_prefix = str_repeat('../', $segment_count);
}
```

- **Asset URL usage MUST prepend `$path_prefix`**

```php
<link rel="stylesheet" href="<?php echo $path_prefix; ?>css/global.css">
<script src="<?php echo $path_prefix; ?>js/modal_a11y.js"></script>
```

- **Root navigation links MUST target the application root**
  - `V:\includes\header.php` uses `$app_root = '/'` and links `href="<?php echo $app_root; ?>index.php"`.
  - When generating “home” links from any subdirectory, prefer `href="<?php echo $path_prefix; ?>index.php"` (footer pattern) or the established `$app_root` usage (header pattern), depending on context.
